libgit2
------------------------------------------
libgit2 is a portable, pure C implementation of the Git core methods provided
as a re-entrant linkable library with a solid API, allowing you to write
native speed custom Git applications in any language which supports C
bindings.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.17-1
  openssl-devel-1.0.1c-2
  zlib-devel-1.2.7-1
  zlib0-1.2.7-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.22.51-2
  cmake-2.8.9-2
  cygport-0.11.2-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-3
  make-3.82.90-1

Canonical website:
  http://libgit2.github.com/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/downloads/libgit2/libgit2/libgit2-0.17.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libgit2-0.17.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libgit2-0.17.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libgit2-0.17.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgit2-0.17.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgit2_0-0.17.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgit2-devel-0.17.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

